.TH ABRAFLEXI-REPXMLUNPACKER 1 "2025-09-20" "abraflexi-report-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
abraflexi-repxmlunpacker \- create a JasperStudio project from an AbraFlexi report export
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B abraflexi-repxmlunpacker
.I abraflexi-reports-import.xml
.I destination-directory
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B abraflexi-repxmlunpacker
extracts an AbraFlexi report installation XML file into a JasperStudio project
directory structure.
It creates Eclipse project metadata, populates a Java classpath referencing the
installed AbraFlexi libraries, and writes each exported report and attachment to
its own directory.
.PP
Attachments embedded in the source XML are decoded from Base64 and written next
to the extracted report metadata.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I abraflexi-reports-import.xml
Source XML file exported from AbraFlexi containing one or more reports.
.TP
.I destination-directory
Directory where the JasperStudio project should be created.
The tool appends the XML filename stem as the project directory name.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/abraflexi/lib/
Used to determine installed AbraFlexi library version and populate the generated
.I .classpath
file.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Extract a report bundle into a Jasper workspace:
.B abraflexi-repxmlunpacker abraflexi-reports-import.xml /path/to/jasper/workspace/
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR abraflexi-upreport (1),
.BR abraflexi-updatejasperclasspath (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Vítězslav Dvořák
